# A `.pubignore` overrides the `.gitignore` in the SAME directory for `pub
# publish` (dart.dev/go/pubignore). So this file must mirror the root
# `.gitignore` patterns, otherwise build output, IDE files, etc. leak into the
# published archive. Keep it in sync with `.gitignore`.

# --- mirror of .gitignore ---
# Miscellaneous
*.class
*.log
*.pyc
*.swp
.DS_Store
.atom/
.buildlog/
.history
.svn/

# IntelliJ related
*.iml
*.ipr
*.iws
.idea/

# Flutter/Dart/Pub related
/pubspec.lock
**/doc/api/
.dart_tool/
.packages
build/

# --- package-specific exclusions ---
# Internal architecture decision records — kept in the repo, not shipped.
docs/decisions/

# Documentation screenshots — kept in the repo for the README/docs, but big and
# binary, so not shipped. pub.dev rewrites README's relative image links to the
# `repository` URL (GitHub raw), so they still render on the package page.
docs/screenshots/
